JOHANNESBURG The court case against terror-accused twins Brandon-Lee and Tony-Lee Thulsie has been postponed to April 25.Magistrate Peter du Plessis granted the State a postponement in the case to gather additional evidence from international law enforcement agencies. Magistrate Du Plessis says the State and Defence need to come to an agreement what date to serve the indictment. #ThulsieTwinsThe State is banking on securing evidence obtained during arrests in the UK and Kenya allegedly linked to the Thulsie twins case. Mag: Another issue now before this court is whether or not the #ThulsieTwins were prematurely arrested.READ: Terror-accused Thulsie twins trial delayed againThe twins are facing three counts of contravening the Protection of Constitutional Democracy Against Terrorist and Related Activities Act.They were arrested in July 2015. eNCA